Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: #1 - pornography sights found on defendant's computer

Both parties have reviewed the PSI and Psychological reports.  One correction to PSI on Page 20.  No testimony by defense.  Chris Gamm sworn and testifies for the State.  No cross.  James Darling sworn and testifies for the State.  Cross-exam by Attny Zilles.  Re-direct.  Attny Hepburn sworn and testifies via phone call, represents victims of the Vickie Series & Marine Land Series and requests $5,000.00 restitution for each.  Cross by Attny Zilles.  Arguments as to penalty by DA and defense.  Defendant makes a statement.  Defendant not eligible for ERP or CIP.  Court makes a statement and sentences defendant to a total of 15 years confinement and 10 years extended supervision with specific conditions as noted in the JOC.  Voting and firearms restrictions noted.  DA keeps his PSI & Dr. report, Attny Zilles returns to the Court.  Appeal rights.
